FeedPackage.Description:
A convenient ADO.NET abstraction that implements modern best practices for interacting with databases.
Goals:
1. Native support for AspNet 5, Microsoft's Open Source Dependency Injection framework, and Visual Studio 2015.
2. Use of design patterns to allow easy behavior changes to suit developers' unique interests.
3. Minimal, clean code.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Replaced old DataConnector namespaces with AdoGlue namespace.
Added convenient Stored Procedure extension methods to shortcut their use on IDatabase.
Added convenient virtual DbCommand class for handling all DB calls (stored procedures, ad-hoc, etc) with inheritance point-cuts for tweaking behavior as needed.
As always, please submit feedback (Contact Owners link on left) to suggest changes.

FeedPackage.Description: Uses conventions to map stored procedure parameters and return types when making ado calls with the ability to override conventions.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: A stored procedure is represented as a poco class where every property name and type matches the respective params on the procedure. The columns returned will be automatically hydrated to the specified class type if its properties match the column names. Output params are mapped if the property name on the poco is prepended with Output. Properties on the hydrated class that do not follow convention can be mapped by creating a class inheriting PropertyImpedanceMapper<TClass> for each property.
FeedPackage.Summary: A micro framework that takes the pain out of adding params and mapping returned tables when using stored procedures with ado.net.
FeedPackage.Title: adotic
